abstract: Artist Andrew Kuo reflects on the past two decades after Nirvana’s Nevermind and the documentary 1991: The Year Punk Broke; considers what it all meant and if his younger self was right about how things would turn out.
snippet: Two decades after Nirvana’s “Nevermind” and the documentary “1991: The Year Punk Broke” had an imprinting effect on him as a teenager, the artist Andrew Kuo considers what it all meant.
lead_paragraph: Two decades after Nirvana’s “Nevermind” and the documentary “1991: The Year Punk Broke” had an imprinting effect on him as a teenager, the artist Andrew Kuo considers what it all meant.

headline.seo: Andrew Kuo Looks Back at the Punk of 1991
